CATEGORIES:children,play,toddler,museum,family
DESCRIPTION:Organizer: Pretend City Children's Museum - Events\\nAges: 0-6
 0 months\\nCategory: Play & Games\\n\\nCelebrate Earth Day at Pretend City
  with activities that help children learn how to care for our planet. Fami
 lies are invited to explore simple\, hands-on experiences that highlight n
 ature\, conservation\, and everyday ways we can all help protect the Earth
 . \n\nTIMES: 11 AM &amp\; 2:30 PM\n\n*Members do not require a reservatio
 n.\n*Events and dates are subject to change.\n\nAbout the play partner:\n\
 nOC Waste &amp\; Recycling serves the County’s solid waste disposal need
 s by providing waste management services\, operating public landfills\, pr
 otecting the local environment\, investing in renewable energy enterprise
 s and promoting recycling in order to ensure a safe and healthy communi
 ty for current and future generations. OCWR also provides education\, outr
 each\, and sustainability programs that help residents reduce waste and su
 pport state and local mandates.\\n\\nMore info: https://www.pretendcity.or
 g/events/earth-day-in-the-city/
LOCATION:Pretend City Children's Museum - Events\, 29 Hubble\, Irvine\, CA
 \, 92618
URL:https://www.pretendcity.org/events/earth-day-in-the-city/
